Enzyme Assay: The aim of this assay is to determine the affinity of a test compound for the mPGES-1 enzyme. 47 l of recombinant human mPGES-1 (0.5 g protein/well) containing microsomal suspension in a buffer containing GSH, (2.5 mmol/L L-Glutathione reduced, dissolved in 0.1 mol/L Phosphat Buffer pH 7.4) is dispensed in a 384-well plate and thereafter 1 l of the test compound(s) is/are added and incubated for 25 minutes at room temperature. The enzyme reaction is started by the addition of 2 ul PGH2 (final conc 2 M) disolved in water-free Diglyme. After 60 seconds the reaction is terminated by addition of a stop solution containing FeCl2 (10 L 0.074 mol/l FeCl2). The samples are diluted between 1:25 in PBS (Phosphate Buffered Saline). 10 l of the diluted samples are transferred to 384-well low volume plate.

After 60 seconds the reaction is terminated by addition of a stop solution containing FeCl2 (10 L 0.074 mol/l FeCl2). The samples are diluted between 1:25 in PBS (Phosphate Buffered Saline). 10 l of the diluted samples are transferred to 384-well low volume plate.

After 60 seconds the reaction is terminated by addition of a stop solution containing FeCl2 (10 L 0.074 mol/l FeCl2). The samples are diluted between 1:25 in PBS (Phosphate Buffered Saline). 10 l of the diluted samples are transferred to 384-well low volume plate.

After 60 seconds the reaction is terminated by addition of a stop solution containing FeCl2 (10 L 0.074 mol/l FeCl2). The samples are diluted between 1:25 in PBS (Phosphate Buffered Saline). 10 l of the diluted samples are transferred to 384-well low volume plate.

After 60 seconds the reaction is terminated by addition of a stop solution containing FeCl2 (10 L 0.074 mol/l FeCl2). The samples are diluted between 1:25 in PBS (Phosphate Buffered Saline). 10 l of the diluted samples are transferred to 384-well low volume plate.

After 60 seconds the reaction is terminated by addition of a stop solution containing FeCl2 (10 L 0.074 mol/l FeCl2). The samples are diluted between 1:25 in PBS (Phosphate Buffered Saline). 10 l of the diluted samples are transferred to 384-well low volume plate.

After 60 seconds the reaction is terminated by addition of a stop solution containing FeCl2 (10 uL 0.074 mol/l FeCl2). The samples are diluted between 1:25 in PBS (Phosphate Buffered Saline). 10 ul of the diluted samples are transferred to 384-well low volume plate.

Inhibition Assay: mPGES-1 microsome fractions were prepared from CHO-K1 cells transiently transfected with plasmid encoding the human mPGES-1cDNA. Microsomes were diluted with potassium phosphate buffer containing reduced glutathione (pH7.4), and DMSO containing test compound or DMSO alone was added (such that DMSO final concentration would be 1% in each) and incubated at 4 C. for 20 minutes. Then, the enzymatic reactions were initiated by the addition of PGH2 substrate (final concentration 1 M) and incubated at 4 C. for 60 seconds. The reaction was terminated by the addition of a citrate solution (final citrate concentration 50 mM) containing ferric chloride (final concentration 1 mg/mL). PGE2 production in the enzyme reaction aliquot was measured using HTRF kit (Cisbio International, catalogue #62P2APEC).

Then, the enzymatic reactions were initiated by the addition of PGH2 substrate (final concentration 1 M) and incubated at 4 C. for 60 seconds. The reaction was terminated by the addition of a citrate solution (final citrate concentration 50 mM) containing ferric chloride (final concentration 1 mg/mL). PGE2 production in the enzyme reaction aliquot was measured using HTRF kit (Cisbio International, catalogue #62P2APEC).
